risdiction, without limiting the powers otherwise con-\nferred by this Act or the General Rules,\n(a) to hear bankruptcy applications and to make\nbankruptcy orders if they are not opposed;\n(b) to hold examinations of bankrupts or other per-\nsons;\n(c) to grant orders of discharge;\n(d) to approve proposals where they are not opposed;\n(e) to make interim orders in cases of urgency;\n(f) to hear and determine any unopposed or ex parte\napplication;\n(g) to summon and examine the bankrupt or any per-\nson known or suspected to have in his possession\nproperty of the bankrupt, or to be indebted to him, or\ncapable of giving information respecting the bankrupt,\nhis dealings or property;\n(h) to hear and determine matters relating to proofs\nof claims whether or not opposed;\n(i) to tax or fix costs and to pass accounts;\n(j) to hear and determine any matter with the consent\nof all parties;\nles pouvoirs et la juridiction, sans restriction des pou-\nRègles générales :\nordonnances de faillite, lorsqu’elles ne sont pas\ncontestées;\nb) d’interroger des faillis ou d’autres personnes;\nd) d’approuver des propositions concordataires, lors-\ne) de rendre des ordonnances provisoires dans les cas\nd’urgence;\ng) de sommer et d’interroger le failli ou toute per-\nsonne connue comme ayant en sa possession ou soup-\nses biens;\nou non;\nPowers of Registrar Pouvoirs du registraire\nSection 192 Article 192\nCurrent to/uni00A0August/uni00A011, 2025\nLast amended on December 12, 2024\n(k) to hear and determine any matter relating to prac-\ntice and procedure in the courts;\n(l) to settle and sign all orders and judgments of the\ncourts not settled or signed by a judge and to issue all\norders, judgments, warrants or other processes of the\ncourts;\n(m) to perform all necessary administrative duties re-\nlating to the practice and procedure in the courts; and\n(n) to hear and determine appeals from the decision\nof a trustee allowing or disallowing a claim.\ni) de taxer ou de fixe